<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Paramere quadrangle-shaped in lateral view, with ca 3 sensillae medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Scaptodrosophila sinuata sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416847" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">12A, B</figureCitation>
); gonopods large, with many finely acanthoid processes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Scaptodrosophila sinuata sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416847" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">12C, D</figureCitation>
); aedeagus beanpod-shaped in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Scaptodrosophila sinuata sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416847" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">12C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
(♂) 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. serrateifoliacea sp. nov. B, D, F S. sinuata sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416840" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5B</figureCitation>
): Frons yellowish brown. Pedicel yellow. First flagellomere yellowish brown. Arista weak. Facial carina yellowish, developed, 1/2 length as face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. serrateifoliacea sp. nov. B, D, F S. sinuata sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416840" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5D, F</figureCitation>
): Mesonotum and scutellum yellowish. Acrostichal setulae in ca 8 irregular rows. Halter yellowish brown. Wings light brown and appreciably hyaline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. serrateifoliacea sp. nov. B, D, F S. sinuata sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416840" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5D, F</figureCitation>
): Tergites yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male terminalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Scaptodrosophila sinuata sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416847" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">12</figureCitation>
): Epandrium with ca 23 setae near posterior margin and ventral corner on each side (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Scaptodrosophila sinuata sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416847" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">12A, B</figureCitation>
). Surstylus broad, with ca 12 fine peg-like prensisetae on caudal margin, and numerous setae on outer and inner surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Scaptodrosophila sinuata sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416847" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">12A, B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium pubescent near paramedian setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Scaptodrosophila sinuata sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416847" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">12C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
